items.summary: Talks at Andela | Timirah James - Developer Advocate, Cloudinary
items.description:
Our monthly Talks at Andela webinar kicks off on a high this year!

PS: This year, we get to open up the live webinars to the public tech ecosystem! Feel free to share the details with your networks to join us!

This month we get to host one amazing influencer in the tech evangelism space!

Timirah James, Developer Advocate - Cloudinary
Discussing: Personal Branding for Developers

As developers, we tend to assume that all of our value relies solely upon our skill sets. We lean on our skills to speak for us. What if there’s something even more powerful than that? What if your NAME spoke for your skills? Your personal brand can have the power to unlock many doors and expand your growth both professionally and personally...

Join us as we speak about building your brand to a level where people associate your name with your skills and ultimately, your purpose.

Zoom --> bit.ly/andelaTalksWithCloudinary

Questions --> bit.ly/andela-talks-qa


++++

Timirah James is a Developer Advocate at Cloudinary and an influencer in the evangelism space, creating awareness around STEM and diversity in tech as well as helping others build great technical skills and become great developers. She is an active contributor in the mobile and serverless community and is best known for being a leader in the Los Angeles and Silicon Beach tech community and mentoring through TechniGal LA, her meetup group for women exploring the world of STEM. 

Fun Fact: She is also a noted singer-songwriter and recently released “Coderitis,” a song about her love for technology and innovation, which can be found on SoundCloud and Spotify.

++++

items.summary: International Women's Day Interview with Dayo Olopade
items.description:
Andelans,

To celebrate Women’s History Month and International Women’s Day, we are welcoming Dayo Olopade to Andela on March 11, in a one-hour interview and Q&A led by Donna Mwiine and Rehema Kahurananga.

Dayo is currently the Content Partnerships Lead at YouTube. Prior to her current role, Dayo has led partnerships for both Facebook and Google, and also built a next-gen news app for the New York Times. She’s the author of The Bright Continent (2014), a book on innovation, technology, and opportunity in sub-Saharan Africa, that was adapted for film in 2016. Dayo completed her JD/MBA as a Knight Law and Media Scholar at Yale.

This session will be fully-remote, you can join using the Zoom details. Read her full bio here & come prepared with your questions.

See you there! 


TIA, 
Christina
